The paper deals with the extension of the uncertainty principle to signals on graphs, which involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT), spectral analysis (cs.SI), and graph theory (cs.DS). The authors also discuss the choice of distance function, which is a common topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and machine learning (cs.LG).
